    <p>“So You Want To Be An Au­thor” Vir­tual Mas­ter­class</p>
    <p>This class by Can­did Cre­ation Pub­lish­ing, an in­de­pen­dent English-Chi­nese pub­lish­ing house, con­sists of six mod­ules tai­lored to help writ­ers who as­pire to be­come pub­lished au­thors of non-fic­tion books. Par­tic­i­pants will be guided to de­velop their own blue­print for pub­lish­ing suc­cess us­ing the 6P Pub­lish­ing Frame­work.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Sept 25, 9.30am AD­MIS­SION: $298</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/33dZmp7</p>
    <p>Ji­wang Flow: A Move­ment Work­shop</p>
    <p>Ji­wang is Malay slang for overly sen­ti­men­tal. Par­tic­i­pants will learn how to use their voices and sen­ti­men­tal songs as a re­lease and ob­serve the ef­fect this has on a per­for­mance.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Rumah P7:1SMA, 03-01 Stam­ford Arts Cen­tre MRT: Bugis WHEN: To­mor­row, 5pm AD­MIS­SION: Free with reg­is­tra­tion INFO: bit.ly/3ii2t5R</p>
    <p>Wood-fired Ar­ti­san Bread Work­shop</p>
    <p>In this farm-to-ta­ble ex­pe­ri­ence, par­tic­i­pants get hands-on in bread-mak­ing. They learn to make rus­tic bread and cin­na­mon rolls and have them baked in the spe­cial­ity Earth Oven. Suit­able for all ages. Par­tic­i­pants can bring one child</p>
    <p>(up to age 12) at no ad­di­tional fee. WHERE: Kam­pung Kam­pus, Ground-Up Ini­tia­tive, 91 Lorong Chen­charu (Yishun) MRT: Khatib WHEN: To­mor­row & Satur­day, 9.30am - 1.30pm AD­MIS­SION: $120 INFO: bit.ly/3mdPLrp</p>


